<ce:para>Aberrant DNA methylation is a common observation in various types of human cancers, i.e., breast and lung cancers. Nevertheless, the current DNA methylation detection approaches require bisulfite treatments and are laborious or costly to perform. To address these challenges, we developed a methyl-probe based on the MBD1 protein. Combined with fluorescence correlation spectroscopy, our probe can sensitively detect the existence of DNA methylation at concentrations above 20. nM in a one-pot assay. The probe can quantify the total amount of methylated CG dinucleotides above ~20. nM, independent of DNA sequence contexts, concentrations (20-1900. nM) and methylation levels (5-100%). Our detection platform offers a simple and cheap alternative DNA methylation detection approach. Â© 2014 Elsevier B.V.</ce:para>
